This paper discusses the creation, representativity, potential biases, stability, and overlap between top lists used in research areas such as Internet measurement, privacy, and network security. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Science and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of using top lists on scientific studies, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of top lists in network security (cs.NI), cybercrime (cs.CY), and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
